President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8pm on Monday evening on developments in the country’s fight against COVID-19. Video: President Cyril Ramaphosa to address the nation on Monday evening  In his address last month, Ramaphosa announced government’s intention to lift the national state of disaster that came into effect two years ago. President Ramaphosa addresses the nation [22 March 2022]  South Africa has been under a state of disaster since the country recorded its first COVID-19 case in March 2020. South Africans have been invited to comment on the COVID-19 draft regulations before the 16th of this month.